{"id":14880719,"mediaExerciseId":"e0905ed4-f721-4694-98c4-d6eeac8ef0bc","exerciseName":"5","chapterName":"1","chapterTitle":"Introduction To Corporate Finance","groupId":612257,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":17,"solutions":[{"id":5882255,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we are required to determine the two distinct groups that report to the chief financial officer.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/14/e59b441000aff3edc99a2d92e579911a/fec8ad6c375c4ab4d8d827631f05ddb5/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/14/e59b441000aff3edc99a2d92e579911a/fec8ad6c375c4ab4d8d827631f05ddb5/lateximg.png","width":497}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Before we begin, let us first define corporate finance.\n\n**Corporate finance** is an area in finance that deals with sources of funding, capital structuring, and investment decisions.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/14/e59b441000aff3edc99a2d92e579911a/c5cb52deb7da17355aac7c81c89eb156/lateximg_large.png","width":1000},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/14/e59b441000aff3edc99a2d92e579911a/c5cb52deb7da17355aac7c81c89eb156/lateximg.png","width":500}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"The two distinct groups that report to the chief financial officer are: 1.)  **Treasurer's office**; and 2.) **Controller's office**.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":70,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/14/e59b441000aff3edc99a2d92e579911a/424f90627108e4464377cf9b27ed6498/lateximg_large.png","width":992},"regular":{"height":35,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/14/e59b441000aff3edc99a2d92e579911a/424f90627108e4464377cf9b27ed6498/lateximg.png","width":497}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"1.)  **Treasurer's office** is responsible for cash and credit management, budget and investment, and the financial affairs of the company. \n\nTherefore, the treasurer's office focuses on corporate finance.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/14/e59b441000aff3edc99a2d92e579911a/2ab90a69ddbc36ee5ae199dba9b1209e/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/14/e59b441000aff3edc99a2d92e579911a/2ab90a69ddbc36ee5ae199dba9b1209e/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"2.) **Controller's office** is responsible for accounting and record keeping for the company, tax reporting, and management of information systems.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":68,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/14/e59b441000aff3edc99a2d92e579911a/269d09364a076c967edf0bf0040a2bf1/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/14/e59b441000aff3edc99a2d92e579911a/269d09364a076c967edf0bf0040a2bf1/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"a2922e42-787e-43d4-8fe1-7428798a6766","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":5},{"id":6374875,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we will discuss the two distinct groups that report to the chief financial officer and which group is the focus of corporate finance.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Let us explain what corporate finance is and who is a chief financial officer. Corporate finance is the study of financial decisions made by corporations, such as investment, financing, dividends, and day-to-day operations. A chief financial officer is a senior executive who is in charge of a company's financial operations.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"The two organizational units that report directly to the chief financial officer are:\n\n- Treasurer's office\n\n - Controller's office","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"The **treasurer's office** is in charge of managing cash and credit, capital budgeting, and financial planning. **The controller's office**, is responsible for theÂ expense and corporate finance, information systems and tax management. We can conclude that corporate finance research is concentrated within the functions of the treasurer's office.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"743be7c3-a75c-4d2c-9ebb-7251a6aadbde","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880720,"exerciseName":"6","page":18,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"69418a88-a578-49f3-8cf8-747939f9acb0","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-1-critical-thinking-questions-6-69418a88-a578-49f3-8cf8-747939f9acb0"},{"id":14880721,"exerciseName":"7","page":18,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"afbf8577-59fe-4c13-ae7d-d2964b0ba1da","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-1-critical-thinking-questions-7-afbf8577-59fe-4c13-ae7d-d2964b0ba1da"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14880718,"exerciseName":"4","page":17,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"32878eae-fb41-4406-a11c-15a8470188ed","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-1-critical-thinking-questions-4-32878eae-fb41-4406-a11c-15a8470188ed"},{"id":14880717,"exerciseName":"3","page":17,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"24be9f4b-818d-4358-a920-07b478bc3dee","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-1-critical-thinking-questions-3-24be9f4b-818d-4358-a920-07b478bc3dee"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-1-critical-thinking-questions-5-e0905ed4-f721-4694-98c4-d6eeac8ef0bc"}